    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nMany users want `:restart` to restore their session and window/tabpage layout, so they need to implement a custom command or mapping:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<leader>R', function()\n  local session = vim.fn.stdpath('state') .. '/restart_session.vim'\n  vim.cmd('mksession! ' .. vim.fn.fnameescape(session))\n  vim.cmd('restart source ' .. vim.fn.fnameescape(session))\nend, { desc = 'Restart Neovim' })\n```\n\n(Discussed in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32484#issuecomment-2692882602 , https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33953#discussion_r2119559364 )\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- `:restart!` (bang) restarts without saving session\n- `:restart` (no bang) provides \"DWIM\" behavior for restart:\n    - saves/restores session\n        - respects the current session, if any (`v:this_session`)\n        - if `v:argv` already contained `-S`, show a warning? Or is `v:this_session` a reliable indicator of that?\n    - saves/restores window layout\n    \n> [!NOTE]\n>  \n> Using `:mksession` and 'shada' is OK as an initial \"best effort\" approach. But their limitations may disappoint some users who expect `:restart!` to be more seamless. Session improvements are tracked in:\n> \n> - https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32471\n> - https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34204\n\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "To add to the \"Expected behavior\", I would say that it should probably also respect the current session. I.e. if there was `:source my-session` (can be decided by `v:this_session`), then `:restart!` should save `my-session` and restore it later.\n\nHere is [my current iteration](https://github.com/nvim-mini/mini.nvim/blob/69b7433355664cf76898eb86a12a019f39bd86d1/lua/mini/sessions.lua#L348-L379) of how I think \"restart but preserve current session\" should work. So far an experience is good. There are some rough edges around how sessions interact with special plugin-specific buffers (unlisted and/or `buftype ~= ''`), but it is already an improvement.",
