            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "With #40186 merged, it is possible to configure `:restart` to have this behavior:\n\n```lua\nlocal session_file = vim.fs.joinpath(\n  vim.fn.stdpath('cache') --[[@as string]],\n  'session.tmp.vim'\n)\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('VimLeave', {\n  callback = function()\n    if vim.v.exitreason == 'restart' then\n      vim.cmd.mksession { session_file, bang = true }\n    end\n  end,\n})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('UIEnter', {\n  once = true,\n  callback = function()\n    if vim.v.startreason == 'restart' then\n      vim.cmd.source { session_file }\n      vim.fs.rm(session_file)\n    end\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nLimitations:\n- Race condition if two separate Nvims `:restart` at the same time. It is possible to avoid this by comparing client pids, [like I do in my config](https://github.com/superatomic/nvim/blob/4039156bec835165ef23b13ebed9461998232813/plugin/sessions.lua#L2-L10), but doing so is UI dependent (the default TUI supports this though).\n- No way to restart without restoring a session (short of removing the autocommand).\n- Changes the current session (I'm sure it's possible to integrate with [`mini.sessions`](https://github.com/nvim-mini/mini.sessions) to avoid this; I just don't use sessions, so I didn't care to handle this).\n\nOf course, an actual implementation in core would solve these limitations, but for those who just want `:restart` to \"DWIM\", this works well enough.\n\n---\n\n> sure, we can change in 0.12.2. to avoid rushing session-restore in 0.12.2, for now we could just show an error for the non-bang variant.\n\nLooks like this was missed for 0.12.2 (and 0.12.3). Do we still want to do this for 0.12.4?",
