        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> [@echasnovski](https://github.com/echasnovski) I've started on [#40321](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40321) which is basically a port of mini sessions right now. Let me know if that's something you wanted to work on yourself.\n\nFine by me, both on working on it and upstreaming 'mini.sessions' approach (although it would probably require quite a bit of morphing to fit in core).\n\nNote, that there are still some edge case issues with it, mostly about handling non-file buffers (they are mostly preserved, but may be without content). Saying that \"this is just how `:mksession` works\" is more or less fine, but I'd expect native solution to be more polished.",
